HEADWORD: Sponsional
<hw>Spon"sion*al</hw> <pr>(-⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to a pledge or agreement; responsible.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is righteous even in that representative and
<qex>sponsional</qex> person he put on.</q> <rj><qau>Abp.
Leighton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sponson</ent>⟦br⟧
